      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>Slaughter B. Bullock was born 17 February 1813 in
         Spotsylvania County, Virginia, to James (1760-1836) and Sarah
         Bullock (1775-1842). He married Louisa W. Vaughan (b. 1819) 23
         March 1837 and they had 8 girls and 2 boys. Bullock was a
         farmer in Spotsylvania County, then in the 1850s, he moved his
         family to Hanover County, Virginia, where he continued to
         farm. After the Civil War, he began work as a carpenter.
         Slaughter B. Bullock died 2 March 1883.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>An agreement, dated 17 June 1865, between Slaughter B.
         Bullock (1813-1883) of Hanover County, Virginia, and his
         former slaves, in which Bullock pays wages and provides board
         for his former slaves in return for their labor.</p>
      </scopecontent>
